items.definition: Sea surface wave peak directional spread analysed by spectral method.

prefLabel._value: Spectral directional spread of wave peak on the water body

items.definition: Period corresponding to the wave with maximum height in the record analysed by zero crossing method.

prefLabel._value: Period of the highest wave on the water body

items.definition: The square root of ratio of the zeroth and second-order moment of the non-directional wave spectrum analysed by spectral method.

prefLabel._value: Mean period at spectral second frequency moment of waves on the water body

items.definition: The square root of ratio of the zeroth and first-order moment of the non-directional wave spectrum analysed by spectral method.

prefLabel._value: Mean period at spectral first frequency moment of waves on the water body

items.definition: Average direction (related to true north) from which the peak period waves are coming from analysed by spectral method.

prefLabel._value: Average direction at spectral maximum of waves on the water body

items.definition: Direction (related to true north) towards which the peak period swell waves are heading, analysed by spectral method.

prefLabel._value: Direction at spectral maximum of swell waves on the water body

items.definition: The wavelength of the peak period swell waves analysed by spectral method. The wavelength is the horizontal distance between repeated features on the waveform such as crests, troughs or upward passes through the mean level.

prefLabel._value: Wavelength at spectral maximum of swell waves on the water body
